<subSubSection id="49C942EEFF803958EBD2C328FB8A5E5B" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="016C1165FF803958EBD2C328FEAA5F03" blockId="46.[227,341,1051,1077]" box="[227,341,1051,1077]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<heading id="5A24A609FF803958EBD2C328FEAA5F03" bold="true" box="[227,341,1051,1077]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" reason="3">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF803958EBD2C328FEAA5F03" bold="true" box="[227,341,1051,1077]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="016C1165FF803958EBD2C37FFB8A5E5B" blockId="46.[226,1437,1100,1389]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
This species was attributed to the extinct genus 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF803958E814C37FFC785F50" authorityName="Frizzell &amp; Lamber" authorityYear="1961" box="[805,903,1100,1126]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Holocentridae" genus="Weileria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beryciformes" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF803958E814C37FFC785F50" box="[805,903,1100,1126]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Weileria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FF803958E884C37FFB105F51" author="Frizzell &amp; Lamber" box="[949,1263,1100,1127]" firstAuthor="Frizzell" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="1 - 25" refId="ref53990" refString="Frizzell D. L. &amp; Lamber C. K. 1961. New genera and species of myripristid fishes, in the Gulf Coast Cenozoic, known from otoliths (Pisces, Beryciformes). Bulletin of the University of Missouri School of Mines and Metallurgy, Technical Series 100: 1 - 25." type="book chapter" year="1961">Frizzell &amp; Lamber (1961)</bibRefCitation>
. This doubtful genus cannot be accepted, because its type species, 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF803958E80CC341FC315FBD" authorityName="Frizzell &amp; Lamber" authorityYear="1961" box="[829,974,1137,1163]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Holocentridae" genus="Weileria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beryciformes" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="louisiana">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF803958E80CC341FC315FBD" box="[829,974,1137,1163]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">W. louisiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Moodys Branch Formation of 
<collectingRegion id="C317DF87FF803958EBD3C3A4FEA65F87" box="[226,345,1175,1201]" country="United States of America" name="Louisiana" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Louisiana</collectingRegion>
, is a doubtful species based on an eroded 
<typeStatus id="DE68AFC7FF803958E80EC3A4FC595F87" box="[831,934,1175,1201]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">holotype</typeStatus>
without true features (
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FF803958EF9DC3A4FAD45F87" author="Nolf" box="[1196,1323,1175,1201]" firstAuthor="Nolf" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" refId="ref55849" refString="Nolf D. 2013. The Diversity of Fish Otoliths, Past and Present. Royal Belgian Institute of Natural Sciences, Brussels." type="book" year="2013">Nolf 2013</bibRefCitation>
). Otoliths of “ 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF803958EA25C38EFED35FE0" box="[276,300,1213,1238]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">M</emphasis>
.” 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF803958EA7DC38EFE725FE0" authorityName="Frizzell &amp; Lamber" authorityYear="1961" box="[332,397,1213,1238]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Holocentridae" genus="Weileria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beryciformes" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cajun">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF803958EA7DC38EFE725FE0" box="[332,397,1213,1238]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">cajun</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have the following combination of features: a small, rounded ostium with restricted anterior extension, a gently curved ventral rim, and a strongly convex outer face that forms a thickset profile in the posterior portion. These features are not seen in the recent genus 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF803958EFB0C23BFAFC5E17" box="[1153,1283,1288,1313]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Holocentridae" genus="Myripristis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beryciformes" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF803958EFB0C23BFAFC5E17" box="[1153,1283,1288,1313]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Myripristis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The species was not uncommon but never abundant in our material. Also, many of the myripristine specimens in the collection are rather eroded and do not allow an identification at species level.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
